Now I cannot tell you much about
this because time is short.

00:48:53.679 --> 00:48:58.894
And the chakra above it, which we call
Agnya Chakra, is the optic thalamus.

00:48:58.894 --> 00:49:05.469
Where the nerves of our two eyes meet,
there in the middle is a center

00:49:05.469 --> 00:49:11.308
through which both the pituitary and
pineal glands are controlled,

00:49:11.308 --> 00:49:14.476
due to which the ego and superego which
is formed in the head of a human being,

00:49:14.476 --> 00:49:23.196
is controlled and apart from this, this
chakra, in it's center, now here, look here

00:49:23.196 --> 00:49:29.847
one is this Agnya Chakra, and here in the
center is the Chakra of Shri Krishna.
This is Shri Krishna's Chakra,

00:49:29.847 --> 00:49:36.805
because this Chakra tells us that when man
raised his neck, he set his eyes towards God.

00:49:36.805 --> 00:49:43.355
As long as his neck was towards the earth, till then
his sight was not towards Virat or God Almighty.

00:49:43.355 --> 00:49:46.914
When he raised his neck, when he became
a human from an animal,

00:49:46.914 --> 00:49:50.893
when he raised his neck, then here in
the throat Shri Krishna resided.

00:49:50.893 --> 00:49:57.904
And Radhaji is the power of Shri Krishna.
You know Ra-Dha, Ra means power, and
Dha means the one who sustains.

00:49:57.904 --> 00:50:04.054
And because of this power, due to this
power only, you become a witness.

